.html#MeasureTheory.IsTightMeasureSet\">MeasureTheory.IsTightMeasureSet</a> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#setOf\">{</a><span class=\"fn\">x</span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#setOf\">:</a> <span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/MeasureSpaceDef.html#MeasureTheory.Measure\">MeasureTheory.Measure</a> <span class=\"fn\">E</span></span> <a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#setOf\">|</a> <span class=\"fn\">∃ <span class=\"fn\">μ</span> ∈ <span class=\"fn\">S</span>, <span class=\"fn\">↑<span class=\"fn\">μ</span></span> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Eq\">=</a> <span class=\"fn\">x</span></span><a href=\"./Mathlib/Data/Set/Defs.html#setOf\">}</a></span>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Filter.html#IsCompact\">IsCompact</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Mathlib/Topology/Defs/Basic.html#closure\">closure</a> <span class=\"fn\">S</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"**Prokhorov theorem**: the closure of a tight set of probability measures is compact.\nWe only require the space to be T2. ","docLink":"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prokhorov.html#isCompact_closure_of_isTightMeasureSet","kind":"theorem","line":495,"name":"isCompact_closure_of_isTightMeasureSet","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/blob/0f1dd7505c3d08b5feb82300ccc73179a457bf51/Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prokhorov.lean#L495-L527"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">theorem</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Mathlib/MeasureTheory/Measure/Prokhorov.html#isCompact_setOf_probabilityMeasure_mass_eq_compl_isCompact_le\"><span class=\"name\">isCompact_setOf_probabilityMeasure_mass_eq_compl_isCompact_le</span></a></span><span class=\"impl_arg\"><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">{<span class=\"fn\">E</span> : <a href=\"./foundational_types.html\">Type</a> u_1}</span